    "<h5><span style=\"font-family: Monospace; color:#7077D7\">Quotes:</span></h5>\n",
    "\n",
    "- If using single quotes and the string has a single quote, Python will read it as the end of a string.\n",
    "- To combat this, use a backslash or double quotes.\n",
    "- Vice versa for double quotes.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "I'm feeling happy\n",
      "I'm feeling sad\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Example: mood1 = 'I'm feeling tired'\n",
    "# Apostrophe in \"I'm\" interrupts string and will cause error\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use backslash in front or double quotes\n",
    "mood2 = 'I\\'m feeling happy'\n",
    "mood3 = \"I'm feeling sad\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(mood2)\n",
    "print(mood3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
